race.comment: Even race to finish the day and quite a few that mix their form. The old war horse FRANCE'S BOY (2) has won 20 races in his career and looks well placed to add a 21st win here. He's drawn well, gets 3kg off and brings the strongest form lines. He will be hard to beat. COPPER BULLET (1) looks a likely improver second-up to 1500m. He's undefeated at Gawler and has a bit more upside than most of his rivals. Jake Toeroek can overcome the wide draw. GRANDELLIE (11) is mixing her form bur off her win two starts ago, she can be somewhere in the finish here. FLYING STEP (7) is better than last start and, if she returns to her previous form, she can fill a top three position, while BYWATERS ROAD (12) looks some chance at double figures.
